cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper proposes a framework for multi-source multi-view clustering, which involves integrating information from multiple sources with different views. This topic is closely related to machine learning and data mining, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category, as the paper proposes a new clustering method based on collective spectral clustering. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are also likely categories, as they often involve multi-view learning and clustering. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category, as the paper deals with incomplete mapping between sources. Finally, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still relevant as the paper proposes a new algorithm for multi-view clustering.
